<HEADLINE> Vietnamese PM on Tasks in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Prime Minster Phan Van
Khai said Saturday that in the New Year, his government will focus
on developing agriculture and rural areas, tackling hindrance in
industrial production with an aim of maintaining the economic
growth rate, mobilizing and effectively utilizing all sources of
investment.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here this afternoon, the prime
minister said activities in external economic relations should be
boosted, while negative factors, especially those in the finance
and banking sectors, should be corrected.
</P>
<P>
He said that the country would continue solving urgent social
issues and reforming the national administrative system.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also pointed out three weak points that
needed to be addressed immediately so as to fulfill the
socio-economic development plan for 1999, namely the economy's low
competitiveness, red tape, and social evils, particularly drug
trafficking and abuse.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Vietnam now was on a new position and had new
strength, and with the precious experiences from over ten years of
carrying out renovation, the country had favorable conditions to
achieve this year's development plan.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of equalization of state-owned enterprises, Khai
affirmed that Vietnam would continue to equalize those
enterprises. The aim of the process was to enhance the key role of
the state-owned enterprises in the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
