<HEADLINE> Lebanon Blasts Israeli Attack Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon on Saturday strongly
condemned the renewed Israeli threat to attack the country's
infrastructure when its north was hit again by Lebanese
guerrillas' Katyusha rockets.
</P>
<P>
"The Israeli threat clearly showed its intention of aggression
against Lebanese civilians," Lebanese Minister of Refugee Affairs
and Information Anwar Khalil told the country's Central News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli threat, which seemed like a respond to Katyusha
attack on its north, was designated in fact to cover its criminal
act against a Lebanese family, seven members of which were killed
in Israeli air raids, he added.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Israeli warplanes raided Lebanon's eastern Bekaa
Valley, killing a woman and her six children. Israel later claimed
that was a "mistake" and made a public apology for the victims.
</P>
<P>
The next day, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
slammed scores of Katyusha rockets into Israeli northern areas in
retaliation, wounding at least 16 Israelis.
</P>
<P>
The development forced the Israeli security cabinet to review
its policy on south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In its meeting last Thursday, the Israeli government decided
to attack Lebanon's infrastructure when its north was hit again by
Hezbollah's rocket attacks.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting against Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
The minister stressed that Lebanon's resistance movement is a
legal right and will continue till the day the country's all
occupied lands were liberated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
