<HEADLINE> 1,843 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,843 rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the military
operations launched by the security forces in eastern and
southeastern Turkey in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Anatolia News Agency Saturday quoted officials as
saying that the security forces also wounded 29 PKK militants and
captured 155 others in their operations in the region last year.
</P>
<P>
And 118 PKK guerrillas surrendered to the government.
</P>
<P>
However, 311 soldiers of the security forces died in the armed
clashes with the PKK rebels.
</P>
<P>
A total of 24 generals and 39,500 government troops
participated in the "Murat Operation", the largest one against the
PKK in the region last April.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war for
autonomy in eastern and southeastern Turkey, which has claimed
over 37,000 lives in conflicts since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
