<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Awards \n\rArtists, Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Fine Arts and
Mass Media Prize Trust Saturday awarded nine artists and journalists for
life time achievement and long time effort at a colorful ceremony in
the capital here.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the award contains gold
medal and diploma with a sum of 20,000 birr (2,666 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
This is the first awarding prizes to artists and journalists since the
Ethiopian Fine Arts and Mass Media Prize Trust was founded in
August 1998.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian President Negasso Gidada handed the awards over to the
nine winners who are composer and arranger of top Amharic and Oromigna
songs Sahle Degago, vocalist Tilahun Gessesse, vocalist Mohamud Ahmed,
painter Taddesse Mesfin, novel writer Sisay negussu, journalist Teshome
Adera, actor Tesfaye Sahilu, singer and actress Asnaketch Worku and actor
Getinet Enyew.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the occasion, Negasso said the Ethiopian government
welcomes efforts to encourage professionals of various disciplines to
contribute their share.
</P>
<P>
He said Saturday's prize winners set a good example to the younger
generation and encouraged them to work harder. 
</P>
