<HEADLINE> Illegal Money Transfer Detected in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers at the Tan Son
Nhat airport in Ho Chi Minh City, the largest city of Vietnam,
detected a Taiwanese passport holder who intended to illegally
bring out of Vietnam 95,000 U.S. dollars on December 29, local
press reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ho Hua Liang, born in 1968, was found hiding 95,000 U.S.
dollars in his luggage while clearing customs procedures for
boarding a Ho Chi Minh City-Taipei flight.
</P>
<P>
The money has been temporarily confiscated and forwarded to
relevant agencies for further investigation.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Vietnamese customs officers totally detected 1 million
U.S. dollars and 45 million Japanese yen (roughly 320,000 U.S.
dollars) being illegally transferred through the airport.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's current effective regulations require declaration by
any one who makes entry in or exit out of Vietnam if he/she brings
along a 3,000 U.S. dollars equivalent amount or 5 million VN dong.
 
</P>
