<HEADLINE> Timely Defusing of Bomb Saves Train Mishap in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The timely defusing of a bomb
weighing six pound saved a passenger train from explosion in
Pakistan's eastern province of Punjab Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The timely defusing of the device planted under the railway
track saved a passenger train from the provincial capital of
Lahore to Sialkot, about 110 kilometers north of the city, from
explosion, said a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan
Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
Police sources were quoted as saying that the bomb was planted
underneath the railway track near Jhodewali, about five kilometers
from Sialkot.
</P>
<P>
The railway guard on patrol duty saw something with a dim light
under the track at 3:30 a.m. (local time) and informed the
district administration, railway authorities and the police,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The bomb disposal squad rushed to the place and defused the
bomb, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report added that the device was defused only 45 minutes
before a crowded Lahore-bound passenger train was to pass.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth bomb placed on this track in the recent
past, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
