<HEADLINE> Rockets Blows Aoshen in Closest Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockets, trailing in most of time and saw their rivals leading
64-51 at halftime, finally handed a 102-101 defeat to visiting
Aoshen, which was coached by former women's international Li Xin.
</P>
<P>
Newly-promoted Aoshen, the Division Two League winner last
season, pulled off a 12-4 run in the opening two minutes as the
defending Division One League champions Rockets apparently failed
to find their form.
</P>
<P>
Suddenly jolted into action, Rockets fought back strongly and
closed the score to 33-35 at the buzz of the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
Aoshen pulled away in the second quarter, leading by 13 points
at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Rockets didn't give in and narrowed the score to three points
at the end of third quarter.
</P>
<P>
The fourth quarter was a seesaw game until Rockets snatched
the last point with four seconds to go to become one of the three
unbeaten teams.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Hunters kept a clean sheet with a 109-84 victory over
Jiangsu Dragons while Shanghai Sharks got their third straight
win by beating Beijing Ducks 97-80.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, Sichuan Pandas nipped Zhejiang
Cyclone 110-104, Jinlin Northeast Tigers downed Jinan Army
Pegasus 101-71, and Guangdong Tigers ousted Shandong Flaming
Bulls 96-89. 
</P>
