<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs Surpasses Tax Collection Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Customs collected tax
revenues totalling 18.9 billion yuan during 1998 in spite of the
financial turmoil engulfing many part of Asia.
</P>
<P>
The figure, which exceeded the target by 6.6 percent, included
levies of 6.77 billion yuan worth of tariffs on import and export
commodities, as well as 12.9 billion yuan in value-added and
consumption taxes on imported commodities.
