<HEADLINE> Premier Zhu On Science and Technology (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China's modernization practices
have proved that economic construction should depend on progress
in the realm of science and technology, according to Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
The premier, who also heads the leading group for scientific
and technological education made the remarks during the group's
third meeting held in Beijing on December 31.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the rapid expansion of contemporary science
and technology has fully demonstrated the correct scientific
foresight of Deng Xiaoping and his contention that "science and
technology are the primary productive forces".
</P>
<P>
"Resolving deep-seated contradictions and problems in economic
construction will depend on improving the level of science and
technology and innovativeness, as well as on improving the
scientific and technological education. Related efforts will
determine the extent of the gap between China and developed
countries," according to the premier.
</P>
<P>
He said that new ideas and measures for scientific and
technological work must be employed to properly handle related
issues.
</P>
<P>
Important jobs at the moment center on advancing reform of the
scientific, technological and education systems, as well as
accelerating development of the innovation system, he said.
</P>
