<HEADLINE> Premier Zhu On Science and Technology (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu stressed the necessity for taking full advantage of the
role of enterprises as one of the main force in industrial
applications of science and technology and bringing it into full
play, and ensuring that enterprises become a principal force of
technological innovations.
</P>
<P>
"Medium- to large-sized enterprises should attach great
importance to scientific and technological progress and improving
the quality of the labor force. They should also intensify
technological development and applications of scientific and
technological achievements while promoting the market potential of
high-tech items and related products," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The premier also cited the need for effective policies to
transform institutes involved in applied scientific research into
development enterprises. He said more scientists and technicians
from research organizations and universities should be encouraged
to work closely with the manufacturing, or otherwise help improve
the technological innovativeness of enterprises by forming
different forms of economic entities.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that related efforts will fundamentally change the
current status of the nation's scientific and technological forces
which are for the most part dissociated from manufacturing
enterprises and the market.
</P>
<P>
Research academies and institutes should also improve the
distribution of resources, expand reform of internal management
systems and release redundant personnel. He called for introducing
measures such as the bid system for research projects in order to
advance the reform of research institutes.
</P>
<P>
"We should use means provided by the socialist market economy
to advance the application of scientific and technological
achievements and form an effective system based on the integration
of science, technology and the economy and production," noted Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Participants discussed a report Minister of Science and
Technology Zhu Lilan presented on preparations for a national work
conference on technological innovations and issues related to the
innovativeness of small- to medium-sized enterprises of the
sector. They also finalized matters concerning a national
conference scheduled for later and discussed another report by
Minister of Education Chen Zhili.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Li Lanqing, deputy director of the leading group
on scientific and technological education, presented a speech on
related issues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
