<HEADLINE> Blatter Suggests World Cup Be Held Every Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- World soccer chief Sepp Blatter
said in Zurich Sunday he wanted to increase the status of
national soccer teams by holding the World Cup finals every two
years.
</P>
<P>
"I am demanding a clear statement: Do we want national teams
or do we only want club football?" said FIFA president,
interviewed in the Zurich weekly SonntagsBlick.
</P>
<P>
He said his plan would see the competition taking place in
all even-numbered years, instead of every four years as at
present.
</P>
<P>
"The existing four-yearly tournament is out-of-date. It dates
from the 1930s when teams chugged from one continent to another
on ships," said Blatter.
</P>
<P>
Qualification for the finals would happen in odd-numbered
years when national teams would take part in continental tou
rnaments.
</P>
<P>
The existing system of qualification, where teams play
international matches in groups over the course of the years
leading up to the finals, would be dropped.
</P>
<P>
The president said that he has already put his idea to the
FIFA executive committee, which is now studying it. Any changes
could not come into force before the year 2006. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
