<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host 13th ICSEI Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will host the 13th
annual meeting of the International Congress for School
Effectiveness and Improvement (ICSEI) next year, official source
said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This would be the first ICSEI meeting ever to be convened in
Asia, a press release issued by the Government Information Service
said.
</P>
<P>
Moses Cheng, chairman of the Board of Education (BoE) of Hong
Kong, who is also the chairman of the organizing committee of the
Hong Kong ICSEI, is leading a four-member BoE delegation in San
Antonio, the United States, to attend the 12th annual meeting of
ICSEI starting January 3 (local time).
</P>
<P>
He will make a presentation in the meeting and invite
participants to join the ICSEI 2000 in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The conference will provide an excellent venue for Hong Kong
participants to strengthen ties with overseas experts in
education, exchange views and stay abreast of developments in
school reforms overseas.
</P>
<P>
Their participation will highly enhance their contribution to
the pursuit of quality school education in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The conference will provide a forum to examine these issues in
an international context, looking at the experiences and policies
of both developed and developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The ICSEI is made up of educational researchers, policy
specialists and school education experts devoted to school
effectiveness and improvement.
</P>
<P>
Their first annual meeting was held in London in
1988. Subsequent meetings have been organized in various cities
around the world, including Rotterdam, Melbourne, Victoria,
Memphis and Manchester. 
</P>
</TEXT>
