<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Airport Handles 100,000 Passengers A Day for 1st Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong International
Airport has established a record of the smooth handling of over
100,000 passengers and their baggage in one day during the
Christmas and New Year holiday season, the Airport Authority (AA)
said today.
</P>
<P>
All passengers services were delivered without any incident
throughout the period of December 19 to January 3, despite the
numbers of passengers and flights were much more than that at Kai
Tak airport during the same period last year, AA officials said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's international airport moved from downtown Kowloon
to Chek Lap Kok at the Lantau island in July last year and met
some troubles at the beginning of the operation.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that some 250 additional flights were operated
during the final two weeks of December and the daily passenger
throughput ranged from about 80,000 to more than an estimated of
100,000 on December 27, the highest daily figure so far at the new
airport.
</P>
<P>
The average daily number of departing and transfer bags also
increased from 33,000 on a normal day to 42,000 during the holiday
period -- an increase of some 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The higher passenger throughput had no impact on the efficiency
of passenger services, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-five percent of all flights continued to leave on time
or within 15 minutes of schedule; 90 percent of passengers waited
no longer than 10 minutes for their bags; and 98 percent of all
arriving and departing passengers completed immigration
formalities within 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Ng Ki-sing, general manager of the Terminal Operations of the
airport, said that the passenger figures are encouraging given the
current economic climate, and the experience during the Christmas
and New Year holidays will prove useful in planning for the
Chinese Lunar New Year period, which traditionally is an even
busier time for air travel in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The airport has recently won the Critics' Choice Award of the
Travel and Leisure magazine, a leading travel magazine in the
United States, for its outstanding performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
