<HEADLINE> Indian Science Congress Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The 86th Indian Science
Congress Opened in Chennai city 2,095 kilometers south of New
Delhi Sunday, the largest annual science gathering in the country.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the meeting, Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee
asked Indian scientists to spend more time on research and must be
prepared to deliver the goods.
</P>
<P>
Outlining a four-pronged strategy for science development in
India, Vajpayee said that Indian scientists must focus not only on
quantity, but also on quality that withstand international
scrutiny. Indian scientists must resolve not to remain recipients
of scientific and technological knowledge from outside, but also
become major contributors.
</P>
<P>
He asked scientists to re-focus on solving problems of Indian
industry and agriculture to create a hunger-free society.
</P>
<P>
He said that another important task before scientists is to
train "our children and young generation" in a spirit of
scientific inquiry.
</P>
<P>
"Looking to the future, India should concentrate on information
technology and biosciences, the two knowledge-based sciences
having the widest possible applications," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Vajpayee also asked Indian scientists not to allow themselves
to be arm-twisted by countries denying technologies and to become
trendsetters by shedding their image of being mere recipients of
technologies. 
</P>
