<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Is Act of Terrorism: Pak Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Information
Minister Mushahid Hussain said the bomb blast on Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif's route Sunday morning is an act of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The government has started investigation into the incident to
identify culprits, Mushahid told the media here after the bomb
blast, adding "this incident has further strengthened our
determination to root out terrorism in the country".
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed and four others injured in the bomb
blast, which took place on a bridge outside Punjab province's
capital of Lahore, only a few kilometers away from Nawaz Sharif's
family estate.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was due to travel along the road about five
minutes later, the police said, adding that it is too early to
draw any connection.
</P>
<P>
The explosive device went off at 9:45 a.m. (local time) at the
bridge on the dual carriageway from Lahore to Raiwind, about 30
kilometers south of the capital city.
</P>
<P>
In the impact, the left side of the Lahore-Raiwind road has
blown off at the site of the occurrence while the right side
carriageway has been badly damaged.  
</P>
