<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Chinese Women favors Pursuit of World Fashion (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Yu Zheng
</P>
<P>
XI'AN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Ancient Chinese women favored the
pursuit of world fashions back 1,200 years ago, according to an
observer of the fashion industry.
</P>
<P>
The pursuit of contemporary fashions centers on the
avant-garde. Dior, a brand-name in the fashion industry, recently
introduced its new line featuring styles popular during ancient
China's Tang Dynasty (618-907).
</P>
<P>
The economic-booming dynasty wanted to incorporate the aspects
of diverse cultures, according to Jia Yun, a researcher at the
Guangzhou Academy of Fine Arts.
</P>
<P>
"The shaping of Western tradition and the ensuing integration
of Chinese and Western cultures," according to Jia, "reflected the
imperceptible process of mutual study and popularity.
</P>
<P>
She said that "fashion trends in Tang Dynasty epitomizes the
cultural panorama of the times."
</P>
<P>
The longstanding peace existent in most periods of the dynasty
enabled people to lead a secure life. And imperial courts helped
create a highly developed economy and mixed culture.
</P>
<P>
Females no longer wore loose-fitting garments that were popular
in the preceding dynasties and they preferred simpler yet stylish
clothing introduced from the West, which subjects in Tang dynasty
referred to as "Hufu" dresses.
</P>
<P>
Hufu was characterized by turned collars, straight sleeves,
chemises, straight slacks and tall boots. Common people preferred
wearing shorter and more flexible trousers similar to those worn
by Persians and Byzantines in the sixth century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990103.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Chinese Women Favors Pursue of World Fashion  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Furthermore, a few stylish women of Tang dynasty could easily
put on elegant garments the same as Italian women did.
</P>
<P>
These garments gave a vivid expression of nomadic features
which heralded a far cry from the Chinese tradition, Jia said.
</P>
<P>
Turndown-collared garments suited swift and violent movements
when riding on horses, she said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, historical records show that the Tang women were
particularly keen to wear boots. But they would replaced high
leather boots by medium-size or lower or even flat ones to fit
their own use.
</P>
<P>
"Only the people fully confident in themselves are eager to
accept things new from outside," Jia said, "and only in peaceful
and relaxed environment can the foreign-imported culture thrive."
</P>
<P>
Besides garments, other things such as pop music, varied
dances, acrobatics, other recreations, food and even poetry then
were greatly influenced by foreign cultures.
</P>
<P>
For a certain period of time, subjects from imperial concubines
to commoners went enthusiastic in performing dances to the
accompaniment of vivid and lively rhythm, just like performing
disco or breakdance in modern times.
</P>
<P>
"Having experienced prolonged wars, the people finally escaped
poverty. They then concerned themselves more with easy way of life
and recreations," Jia said, adding that "their pursuit of novelty
and change among them in turn spurred economic booming and
ideological, political opening-up."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990103.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Southwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- A minor earthquake jolted the
Ninglang Yi Ethnic Group Autonomous County in southwestern Yunnan
province on 1:55 A.M. Beijing time today.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities are investigating into damages of the
quake which is measured 5 on the Richter Scale.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located at 27.2 degrees north latitude, and
101.0 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that strong shocks were felt at Ninglang and
adjacent Yanyuan county in Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Seismological Bureau, the latest quake
was part of the series of earthquakes that started in Ninglang on
October 2, last year.
</P>
<P>
The Seismological Bureau of Yunnan province has sent a
five-member team to the site of the quake to look into
damages and monitor seismic movements.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have so far been reported.  
