<HEADLINE> Philippine Reforms Way of Budget Implementation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 3 (Xinhua) --- The Philippine government will
use a new system on 1999 budget implementation in an effort to cut
graft and speed up the development of vital projects, a
Presidential Palace news release said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Benjamin Diokno, secretary of Budget and Management, was quoted
as saying the new scheme simplifies funds release procedure.
</P>
<P>
To speed up the development of projects, Diokno said his
department will release funds in cash on a quarterly basis rather
than on a monthly basis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Local governments will get the full amount of
their share in the budget, he added.
</P>
<P>
Diokno believed the reform will ensure the government to
release the necessary funds for essential public services on time.
</P>
<P>
It would also ensure transparency, and guarantee the national
budget free from corruption, he said.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Joseph Estrada signed the 1999 budget into
law last December 30 following close coordination between the
executive branch and Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
