<HEADLINE> China's Army-to-Army Foreign Relations Forge Ahead (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Also in 1998, quite a number of senior U.S. military officials,
including a number of former defense secretaries and assistant
secretaries, came to Beijing, and consultations on maritime safety
and defense were held right on schedule, both of which displayed
the mutual trust that has been established between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
In another development, China's military exchanges with its
neighbor Russia exhibited good momentum last year, with a series
of senior Russian army officials, including the Russian defense
minister, coming to Beijing. The two countries acknowledged their
identical or similar stance on world issues, and unanimously
voiced concern over some countries' developing missile defense
system.
</P>
