relations with another important neighbor -- Japan. Chinese
defense minister and the Japanese defense agency director-general
exchanged visits last year, which was the 20th anniversary of the
signing of the Peace and Friendship Treaty between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Army-to-army relations with important countries such as those
in the European Union and Australia and Canada were also enlarged
in 1998, as their level and scope were broadened compared with
those of the last few years.
</P>
<P>
As always, China attached great importance to keeping friendly
military ties with neighboring countries. The PLA dispatched
delegations to 17 neighboring countries last year, while receiving
army leaders from over 10 nations, thus further helping China's
friendly bilateral ties with its neighbors to be strengthened, and
mutual trust to be enhanced.
</P>
