<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada said Saturday that he
would pursue to the hilt his campaign promise this year to rid the
government of misfits and the corruption.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star:
</P>
<P>
-- President Estrada Saturday ordered the dismissal of
policemen who ignored warnings not to fire their guns during New
Year's Eve revelry.
</P>
<P>
Malaya:
</P>
<P>
-- Eleven firefighters were seriously injured Saturday in a
seven-hour fire which gutted a hardware store and several
commercial establishments in Manila.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- The Department of Environment and Natural Resources Saturday
welcomed the assistance extended by the Asian Development Bank to
cleanse Manila of its air pollution problem and to promote policy
reforms to improve air quality. 
</P>
