<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Crack Down on Underworld </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan police have
determined to come down very hard on all underworld criminals from
now on to arrest crime rates, the Sunday Observer reported.
</P>
<P>
The Deputy Inspector General Kotakadeniya told the paper that
they have 30 gang leaders to be dealt with this year as almost all
underworld gangs operate by making Colombo as their base.
</P>
<P>
He urged the public to assist the police in bring them to book.
</P>
<P>
"In most of the instances so far only the cadres have been
rounded up. Men who operate them remain free," Kotakadeniya was
quoted as saying, adding that lack of complaints against kingpins
was the main cause.
</P>
<P>
Kotakadeniya said that anti-money laundering legislation will
be presented in the parliament early this year. Underworld gang
leaders have been considered the main culprits in
money-laundering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
