<HEADLINE> Russia Enters Semis at World Junior Ice Hockey Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Russia upset defending champions
Finland 3-2 on Saturday to enter the semifinals of the World
Junior Ice Hockey Championship in Winnipeg, Canada.
</P>
<P>
Denis Arkhipov scored the winner 7:33 into overtime, revenging
Russia's loss to Finland in last year's final in Helsinki.
</P>
<P>
After Niklas Hagman and Teemu Elomo scored to give Finland 2-0
lead, Roman Liachenko reduced the gap for the Russians while
Dmitri Kirilenko hit the net at 13:47 in the final period to drag
the Finns into overtime.
</P>
<P>
Russia, which finished 3-0-1 during round-robin play in Group
B, meets Slovakia on Monday in the semifinal round. The
Slovakians finished first in Pool A with a 3-1-0 record to earn a
bye into the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Canada and Kazakhstan were to play Saturday night in the other
quarterfinal. The winner takes on Sweden in the other semifinal
on Monday afternoon. Sweden received the bye after finishing atop
Pool B with a perfect 4-0 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
