<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Men Shot Dead in Sicily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Five men were shot dead Saturday
evening in a cafe bar in Vittoria, a town in Italy's southern
Sicily, in an incident which had all the hallmarks of a Mafia
settling accounts.
</P>
<P>
Police said the five men, who were drinking coffee and
reading newspapers in the bar, were killed by two gunmen carrying
large-caliber automatic weapons. The gunmen then fled the scene
by a Fiat car.
</P>
<P>
The manager of the cafe bar, 62, was immediately questioned,
after police arrived.
</P>
<P>
The five victims, aged between 20 and 30, had criminal records
and had been under police watch for suspected involvement in drug
trafficking, police said.
</P>
<P>
The killings, police said, may have been a reaction from the
local Mafia to the young men's failure "to observe the rules" in
trying to carve out a share for themselves in the lucrative drug
smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
