<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Unemployment Reaches 20 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless people
plus people who were laid off from their work in Indonesia now
totals 20 million, more than 22 percent of about 90 million people
in the labor force, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
"The unemployment figure is expected to diminish now that the
government had launched labor-intensive projects with funds taken
from the state budget," Manpower Minister Fahmi Idris said on
Saturday in Denpasar, capital of Bali province, according to
reports reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the funds for the 1998/1999 fiscal year (ends
March 31) labor intensive projects amounted to 1.3 trillion rupiah
(one U.S. dollar equals 8,000 rupiah now).
</P>
<P>
He also hoped the Indonesian economy would improve further so
that the allocation of state budget for the 1999/2000 fiscal year
would increase to cope with unemployment in different areas in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Economic experts estimated that more than 70 million people out
of a population of 202 million have fallen below the poverty line.
Some 30 million of them have experienced absolute poverty by the
end of 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
