<HEADLINE> Rushden and Diamonds Hold Leeds in F.A. Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Minor league Rushden and
Diamonds gave a shock on Saturday, holding mighty Leeds, fifth in
the premier league, to a sparkling 0-0 draw in the English F.A.
Cup third round match.
</P>
<P>
Leeds were reduced to 10 men in the 74th minute when Jonathan
Woodgate picked up a second yellow card but Rushden were never
overawed and could even have gone in at the break unhappy not to
have scored.
</P>
<P>
First division Portsmouth accounted for the premiership scalp
of bottom club Nottingham Forest, winning 1-0, while 10-man
Southampton needed a last-minute goal to hold second division
leaders Fulham 1-1.
</P>
<P>
Third division Swansea came close to upsetting premier league
West Ham, drawing 1-1 at Upton Park after the hosts equalised
through Julian Dicks in the 87th.
</P>
<P>
Charlton Athletic went out 2-0 at Blackburn Rovers in an
all-top flight clash.
</P>
<P>
League leaders Aston Villa beat third division tail-enders
Hull City 3-0 after taking the lead only in first half stoppage
time. Coventry smacked seven past second division Macclesfield
without reply.
</P>
<P>
Newcastle United, finalists last year, suffered an early scare
when they had goalkeeper Shay Given sent off for handling the
ball outside the area in the 14th minute and then went a goal
down to Crystal Palace. Alan Shearer gave Newcastle a 2-1 win.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, second in the league, won 2-0 at second division
Oldham Athletic, player-manager Gianluca Vialli scoring twice.
</P>
<P>
Holders Arsenal play at Preston North End on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
